content:
Runs TypeScript compiler in no-emit mode after editing TypeScript files to immediately catch type errors and compilation issues. Shows clear error messages and prevents bad code from being committed.

```json
{
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Edit|Write",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "if [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *.ts ]] || [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *.tsx ]]; then npx tsc --noEmit \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" && echo '✅ TypeScript compilation successful' || echo '❌ TypeScript compilation failed'; fi"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
